2026-04-30 | Check if Array Represents Max Heap

Question
Return true if array satisfies max heap property.
	Approach
1.	Traverse all non-leaf nodes:
		i from 0 to (n/2 - 1)  
2.	Check:
		if left child exists:
			arr[i] ≥ arr[left]  
		if right child exists:
			arr[i] ≥ arr[right]  
3.	If any violation → return false  
4.	If all satisfied → return true  
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool isMaxHeap(vector<int>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size();
        for(int i = 0; i <= (n/2 - 1); i++){
            int left = 2*i + 1;
            int right = 2*i + 2;
            if(left < n && arr[i] < arr[left])
                return false;
            if(right < n && arr[i] < arr[right])
                return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
};
	Key Insight
In array representation:
		only need to check parent vs children  
No need to check leaves → they have no children  
This ensures efficient validation in O(n).
